The paper deals with the modeling of energy scavenged by photovoltaic panels, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY) and emerging technologies (cs.ET). The methodology presented in the paper involves the use of statistical techniques such as clustering and Markov processes, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the models to communication systems, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
